Amendment No. 1 to HB2091
Todd
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2173 House Bill No. 2091*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 70, Chapter 9, is amended by adding
the following as a new section:
(a) No person shall operate an OHV within the North Cumberland wildlife
management area (WMA) unless the person, or a passenger on the same OHV,
possesses a valid North Cumberland OHV riding permit, a sportsman supplemental
annual North Cumberland OHV riding permit, or a North Cumberland OHV guide permit.
(b) The agency may issue a North Cumberland OHV riding permit to a person
who pays the appropriate permit fee. A North Cumberland OHV riding permit does not
include guide privileges in the North Cumberland WMA. Beginning July 1, 2026, the
North Cumberland OHV riding permit fee is:
(1) Fifty dollars ($50.00) for a nonresident one-day permit;
(2) One hundred twenty-five dollars ($125) for a nonresident three-day
permit;
(3) Two hundred dollars ($200) for a nonresident seven-day permit;
(4) Three hundred dollars ($300) for a nonresident annual permit;
(5) Twenty dollars ($20.00) for a Tennessee resident one-day permit;
(6) Thirty dollars ($30.00) for a Tennessee resident three-day permit;
(7) One hundred dollars ($100) for a Tennessee resident seven-day
permit; and
HA1227
013805
- 1 -

(8) One hundred fifty dollars ($150) for a Tennessee resident annual
permit.
(c)
(1) An annual or lifetime sportsman license issued by the agency does
not include OHV riding privileges in the North Cumberland WMA.
(2) The holder of a valid annual or lifetime sportsman license may
purchase a sportsman supplemental annual North Cumberland OHV riding
permit from the agency. A sportsman supplemental annual North Cumberland
OHV riding permit does not include guide privileges in the North Cumberland
WMA.
(3) The agency may issue a sportsman supplemental annual North
Cumberland OHV riding permit to the holder of a valid annual or lifetime
sportsman license who pays the supplemental permit fee. Beginning July 1,
2026, the sportsman supplemental annual North Cumberland OHV riding permit
fee is forty dollars ($40.00).
(d)
(1)
(A) Except as provided in subdivision (d)(1)(B), a person shall not
accept compensation for assisting others in OHV use while utilizing the
North Cumberland WMA trail system unless the person possesses a valid
North Cumberland OHV guide permit.
(B) A person is not required to possess a North Cumberland OHV
guide permit if the only assistance that the person provides to OHV users
in the North Cumberland WMA is roadside assistance, including, but not
limited to, towing, battery starting and replacement, tire changes, lockout
services, fuel delivery, and winching.
- 2 - 013805

(2) In addition to permitting the privilege of accepting compensation for
assisting others in OHV use while utilizing the North Cumberland WMA trail
system, a North Cumberland OHV guide permit includes the privileges permitted
by a North Cumberland OHV riding permit.
(3) The agency may issue a North Cumberland OHV guide permit to a
person who pays the guide permit fee. Beginning July 1, 2026, the North
Cumberland OHV guide permit fee is seven hundred dollars ($700).
(e) The commission may promulgate rules to adjust the fees established in this
section; provided, that such rules and regulations are consistent with § 70-1-206 and §
70-9-105, and that any increase to fees established in this part shall not become
effective until July 1, 2030.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring it.
